com.midhunarmid.movesapi

Class MovesAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.midhunarmid.movesapi.MovesAPI

  • public class MovesAPI
extends Object
    This class have static methods to deal with all API calls to Moves Server. Use init() method before using any other methods of this library.

    Initialization with init() method requires some details of Client Application which is registered with Moves. You can get all those details while you register your client application.

    Author:
    Midhu
    See Also:
    MovesHandler, How To Create New App

    • Method Detail

      • init

        public static void init(Context context,
        String clientId,
        String clientSecret,
        String clientScopes,
        String redirectURL)
                 throws Exception
        Call this method before using any other functions of this library. Call to this method will initialize your MovesAPI client application details.
        Parameters:
        context - : A valid application Context is required to store data in SharedPreferences
        clientId - : The Client ID you received when registering your application with Moves
        clientSecret - : The Client Secret you received when registering your application with Moves
        clientScopes - : Requested scopes (space-delimited). Should contain either activity, location or both scopes.
        redirectURL - : The URI must match one of the callback URIs registered for your app
        Throws:
        Exception - will thrown if the client details are null or empty

      • destroy

        public static void destroy()
                    throws Exception
        Use when you finished dealing with MovesAPI object. Call to this method will free up all related resources.
        Throws:
        Exception - will thrown if it is already destroyed or never initialized yet.

      • authenticate

        public static void authenticate(MovesHandler<AuthData> handler,
                FragmentActivity parent)
        Use this method to request authorization from Moves. Call to this method will launch the Moves App if it is already installed on the device, or else it will take user through a web page to complete authorization flow.
        Parameters:
        handler - : An implemented MovesHandler with AuthData type. This handler will get notified when the request completes.
        parent - : Call to this method should be initiated from a FragmentActivity. We need to show some DialogFragment while processing authorization flow.

      • getSummary_SingleDay

        public static void getSummary_SingleDay(MovesHandler<ArrayList<SummaryListData>> handler,
                        String date,
                        String updatedSince)
        Get daily activity summaries for user, including step count, distance and duration for each activity (if applicable). Final summary for a particular date will only be available at earliest after midnight in the user’s current time zone.
        Parameters:
        handler - : An implemented MovesHandler with an ArrayList of SummaryListData. This handler will get notified when the request completes.
        date - : date in yyyyMMdd or yyyy-MM-dd format
        updatedSince - : [optional] if set, return only days which data has been updated since given time stamp in ISO 8601 (yyyyMMdd’T’HHmmssZ) format, pass null if not required.
        See Also:
        Moves Developer Page for Daily Summaries

      • getSummary_SpecificWeek

        public static void getSummary_SpecificWeek(MovesHandler<ArrayList<SummaryListData>> handler,
                           String week,
                           String updatedSince)
        Get daily activity summaries for user, including step count, distance and duration for each activity (if applicable). Final summary for a particular date will only be available at earliest after midnight in the user’s current time zone.
        Parameters:
        handler - : An implemented MovesHandler with an ArrayList of SummaryListData. This handler will get notified when the request completes.
        week - : A specific week in yyyy-’W’ww format, for example 2013-W09
        updatedSince - : [optional] if set, return only days which data has been updated since given time stamp in ISO 8601 (yyyyMMdd’T’HHmmssZ) format, pass null if not required.
        See Also:
        Moves Developer Page for Daily Summaries

      • getSummary_PastDays

        public static void getSummary_PastDays(MovesHandler<ArrayList<SummaryListData>> handler,
                       String pastDays,
                       String updatedSince)
        Get daily activity summaries for user, including step count, distance and duration for each activity (if applicable). Final summary for a particular date will only be available at earliest after midnight in the user’s current time zone.
        Parameters:
        handler - : An implemented MovesHandler with an ArrayList of SummaryListData. This handler will get notified when the request completes.
        pastDays - : How many past days to return, including today (in users current time zone)
        updatedSince - : [optional] if set, return only days which data has been updated since given time stamp in ISO 8601 (yyyyMMdd’T’HHmmssZ) format, pass null if not required.
        See Also:
        Moves Developer Page for Daily Summaries
